WIeBXz8mqcV9tEguoQ15w1jZ.text: Turtle is a library that emulates the LOGO environment.

x1Sl46bTPHOA9y5LDBRTX8Tx.text: The user controls a little turtle that carries a pen. By moving and turning the turtle, one can create tons of crazy drawings.

xM5rZrNPLYkZfnKS1uDYGw4T.text: Make sure to call `initialize` once before calling any other turtle command. It resets the turtle environment.

Lyrk9m4O515eDRRKGzARd1rF.text: Use `forward` to move the turtle forward.

bmZARpoYGPfP4Cjwdqui4q5M.text: To go backwards, use a negative distance.

hBR53Xc89Lenq5EebsKOI2UE.text: You can turn the turtle left (counter clockwise) or right (clockwise) by a certain amount of degrees.

moh4NmPckppYvKu2BtYA8I3q.text: The turtle world is centered on a portrait screen. x coordinates go from left to right and y coordinates go from bottom to top.

QPzVWhMexmh9wh5StvfDOHRj.text: You can also use negative angles.

vyFs4i8Mmq35CmOQoIHHOxmO.text: You can change the color of the pen

xgFitYsHW82eiVLw2GT7HWEA.text: You can change the thickness of the pen.

uwR0sd7HVrRHWWU9wKTvgvKw.text: You can lift and put down the pen. When the pen is lifted, the turtle does not draw anything when moving.

ezX7VzNZSPEAmXXx4kBV9AOH.text: Creates the turtle environment and wakes it up!

A5j64jJJLKUMnDZY44k5nZdF.text: Creates the turtle environment and wakes it up!

xM5rZrNPLYkZfnKS1uDYGw4T.text: Make sure to call `initialize portrait` or `initialize landscape` once before calling any other turtle command. It prepares the turtle environment.

ZLQKgp4X2kgG0i2MhESHbMOB.text: It is possible to draw circle efficiently using the `circle` action.

axL6CSiOwZXWZ4wGG8qwGFBg.text: To move without drawing, put the pen 'up'.
To move without drawing, put the pen 'up'. Don't forget to put the pen down to draw again!

HZ3p7SXOPkwzR9LWd8nieYD8.text: Sets the duration of each step in seconds.

x3s585dyMC2CO0mgsZWejXKw.text: The turtle moves fast but you can slow it down by using `slow motion`.

rh3QV4tIg2Ba1ulgNOOd03xz.text: Adds a little pause between each step

aOYri8L64jC1iXFCXVLdX0Cy.text: Moves the turtle to the center of the page coordinates [0 0], pointing up.

ITv82layI9vZNSYZ0xlF5Crc.text: Reports the current turtle's heading in degrees. The degrees correspond to those of a compass; 0 degrees is due North, 90 is East, 180 is South, and 270 is West.

Nrgs741EfVpJ8o9cnbL5Djg3.text: Stands for set heading. Sets the turtle's heading to the specified direction (in degrees). The degrees correspond to those of a compass: 0 degrees is due North, 90 is East, 180 is South, and 270 is West. Right and left turn a turtle a number of degrees from its current heading. Seth makes a turtle point to a specific direction, regardless of its previous heading.

xCAeN2n8h3yYD20Bkk4AKKbB.text: Reports a number representing the pen size in pixels of the current turtle. The maximum is 100.

D4ihCsIhb7XxxhOgyM5K6UQ8.text: Stands for x coordinate. Reports the x coordinate of the current turtle.

e5Eqsqnc12cJO8YLfM1xamE8.text: Stands for y coordinate. Reports the y coordinate of the current turtle.

Paldy9w6oYUsB0mC6bdWtXpq.text: Clears the graphics without changing any turtle's position.

Ci7xrxI12qoSAkLIreutLp4N.text: Clears the graphics on the page and returns the current turtle to its home position, facing up.

Gi4pSBqX7GyinZImuFZctxjx.text: Sets the speed of the turtle in steps per seconds. If zero or negative, the animations are disabled.

xkuWEpDZHh3S5Pb2Tv4TIYug.text: Returns the steps per second. If the result is negative or zero, the moves are not animated.

xLNOUkAFP8u3wWZlyVY2SlEu.text: Sets the x coordinate of the current turtle. The y coordinate remains unchanged.

bGAvDnkDVshRHj5bPEe04Cqg.text: Moves the turtle to the designated x y coordinates. The center of the page is [0 0].
